  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "kind": "summary",
        "title": "Summary",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Compute the sign and (natural) logarithm of the determinant of an array."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "If an array has a very small or very large determinant, then a call to\n`det` may overflow or underflow. This routine is more robust against such\nissues, because it computes the logarithm of the determinant rather than\nthe determinant itself."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "parameters",
        "title": "Parameters",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "a",
            "type": "(..., M, M) array_like",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Input array, has to be a square 2-D array."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "returns",
        "title": "Returns",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "",
            "type": "A namedtuple with the following attributes:",
            "desc_blocks": []
          },
          {
            "name": "sign",
            "type": "(...) array_like",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "A number representing the sign of the determinant. For a real matrix,\nthis is 1, 0, or -1. For a complex matrix, this is a complex number\nwith absolute value 1 (i.e., it is on the unit circle), or else 0."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "logabsdet",
            "type": "(...) array_like",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "The natural log of the absolute value of the determinant."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "",
            "type": "If the determinant is zero, then `sign` will be 0 and `logabsdet`",
            "desc_blocks": []
          },
          {
            "name": "",
            "type": "will be -inf. In all cases, the determinant is equal to",
            "desc_blocks": []
          },
          {
            "name": "",
            "type": "``sign * np.exp(logabsdet)``.",
            "desc_blocks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "notes",
        "title": "Notes",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Broadcasting rules apply, see the `numpy.linalg` documentation for\ndetails."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "The determinant is computed via LU factorization using the LAPACK\nroutine ``z/dgetrf``."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "examples",
        "title": "Examples",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "The determinant of a 2-D array ``[[a, b], [c, d]]`` is ``ad - bc``:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> import numpy as np\n>>> a = np.array([[1, 2], [3, 4]])\n>>> (sign, logabsdet) = np.linalg.slogdet(a)\n>>> (sign, logabsdet)\n(-1, 0.69314718055994529) # may vary\n>>> sign * np.exp(logabsdet)\n-2.0"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Computing log-determinants for a stack of matrices:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> a = np.array([ [[1, 2], [3, 4]], [[1, 2], [2, 1]], [[1, 3], [3, 1]] ])\n>>> a.shape\n(3, 2, 2)\n>>> sign, logabsdet = np.linalg.slogdet(a)\n>>> (sign, logabsdet)\n(array([-1., -1., -1.]), array([ 0.69314718,  1.09861229,  2.07944154]))\n>>> sign * np.exp(logabsdet)\narray([-2., -3., -8.])"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "This routine succeeds where ordinary `det` does not:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> np.linalg.det(np.eye(500) * 0.1)\n0.0\n>>> np.linalg.slogdet(np.eye(500) * 0.1)\n(1, -1151.2925464970228)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
